:: Act 3 - Jane Dead - Dawn {"position":"900,1700","size":"100,100"}
Dawn at the strip mall.

Saul Goodman — real name James McGill, age undisclosed, height whatever the shoes say — unlocks Saul Goodman and Associates.

There are no associates.

He flips on the lights. The Statue of Liberty inflatable on the roof hisses awake through the ceiling. He brews what he calls constitutional coffee, which is just the cheapest grounds at the QuikMart run through twice.

He feels the call coming the way old men feel weather.

(click: ?page)[==
The burner has three missed calls from HEISENBERG.
Two from KID.
(click: ?page)[==
He stares at both names for a long time.

### [DECISION 1] — Who do you call back first?

[[Call Heisenberg - Jane Dead]] 
[[Call the Kid First - Jane Dead]]


:: Call the Kid First - Jane Dead {"position":"750,1850","size":"100,100"}
Voicemail. Of course.

Saul leaves a message in the voice he uses when he's trying to sound calm and isn't:

"Call me back before you call anyone else. That includes nine-one-one. *Especially* nine-one-one. Don't touch anything. Don't talk to anyone. Just — call me back."

(click: ?page)[==
He hangs up and calls Heisenberg.

Walt picks up on the first ring.

*"The girl is dead."*

(click: ?page)[==
Three words. Flat. Like a man reporting weather.

Saul absorbs it the way he absorbs most things — by not absorbing it at all, by filing it immediately into the professional column, by becoming the lawyer in the room even when the room is empty.

(click: ?page)[==
"Go home. Shower. Kiss your wife. Go to work tomorrow. I'll handle the rest."

He hangs up. Calls Mike.

[[The Mike Call - Jane Dead]]


:: Call Heisenberg - Jane Dead {"position":"1050,1850","size":"100,100"}
Walt picks up on the first ring.

*"The girl is dead."*

(click: ?page)[==
Three words. Flat. Not grief. Not panic. Just — information.

Saul absorbs it the way he absorbs most things — by not absorbing it at all. Files it immediately into the professional column.

(click: ?page)[==
"Go home," Saul says. "Shower. Kiss your wife. Go to work tomorrow. I'll handle the rest."

He hangs up and tries the Kid.

Voicemail.

He leaves a message. Calls Mike.

[[The Mike Call - Jane Dead]]


:: The Mike Call - Jane Dead {"position":"900,2000","size":"100,100"}
Thirty seconds flat.

Address. Apartment number. Specific situation.

Mike doesn't do small talk.

"The kid in the apartment too?"

(click: ?page)[==
Saul hears what's inside the question. He knows Mike well enough to know Mike isn't asking because he wants to hurt anyone. He's asking because Mike is thorough and thorough means accounting for all the variables.

But still.

"Do NOT touch the kid."

"I'm not going to touch the kid, Saul."

(click: ?page)[==
Mike hangs up. Saul realizes his hand is shaking on the receiver.

He didn't actually think Mike would. But he had to say it anyway.

That small moment — the fact that he had to say it — is the first crack in the armor this morning.

(click: ?page)[==
Hours pass. Saul doesn't leave the office.

He watches the Statue of Liberty inflate and deflate through the window. He thinks about how he got here. Not this morning — here. How every small professional compromise lines up behind you like cars on a highway until you can't see where the road started.

The burner rings. It's the Kid.

[[Jesse Calls - Jane Dead]]


:: Jesse Calls - Jane Dead {"position":"900,2150","size":"100,100"}
Jesse is crying so hard Saul can't understand him for thirty seconds.

He's trying to say something about Jane. He's trying to say something about waking up and she was just —

"I know," Saul says. "I already know. Listen to me. There's a guy coming to take care of everything. Everything, okay? His name doesn't matter. He's going to make this look like what it is — an overdose. Because it *was* an overdose."

(click: ?page)[==
Jesse starts to ask *did Mr. White —*

"Motel. East side. Now. I'll come to you."

Jesse goes quiet. Then: "Okay."

(click: ?page)[==
Saul sits in the car outside the motel for four minutes before going in.

He tells himself he's thinking about what to say. He isn't. He's stalling. He's been stalling his whole career.

[[The Motel Room - Jane Dead]]


:: The Motel Room - Jane Dead {"position":"900,2300","size":"100,100"}
